<http://human.owl#genid4009> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "A cell that acts in a similar manner to a cytotoxic T cell. It must be activated like a cytotoxic T cell, but the killing is nonspecific and the cell does not need to recognize antigen/MHC on the target cell. This cell is not a T cell and the lineage of the NK cell is not well understood." .
<http://human.owl#genid4911> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Membrane of Reissner" .
<http://human.owl#genid4912> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "A thin layer of tissue that forms the anterior wall of the cochlear duct, which separates it from the vestibular canal." .
<http://human.owl#genid4028> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "The wall of the cochlear duct, which separates it from the scala tympani. It vibrates in response to sound, exciting the hair cells and supports the organ of Corti." .
