<http://human.owl#genid3672> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Natural Killer Cell" .
<http://human.owl#genid3671> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "K lymphocyte" .
<http://human.owl#genid3670> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Killer Cells, Natural" .
<http://human.owl#genid3676> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Natural killer cells are cells that resemble large granular lymphocytes.  They do not express markers of either T or B cell lineage. They are positive for CD16, CD56, and CD 94.  These cells do possess Fc receptors for IgG and can kill target cells using antibody-dependent cell-mediated cytotoxicity. They can also use perforin to kill cells in the absence of antibody and killing may occur without previous sensitization." .
<http://human.owl#genid3675> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Cytotoxic cell" .
<http://human.owl#genid3674> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "killer cells" .
