<http://human.owl#genid1453> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Loose, filamentous areolar connective tissue between the muscularis mucosa and the muscular coat of the small intestine. It contains blood vessels, lymphatics, and nerves. The duodenal submucosa contains mucus-secreting Brunner's glands." .
<http://human.owl#genid1454> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Thyrotroph Cell" .
<http://human.owl#genid7093> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "One of the two organs that excrete the urine. The kidneys are bean-shaped organs (about 11 cm long, 5 cm wide, and 3 cm thick) lying on either side of the vertebral column, posterior to the peritoneum, about opposite the twelfth thoracic and first three lumbar vertebrae." .
<http://human.owl#genid7096> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Sphincter Pupillae Muscle" .
<http://human.owl#genid1451> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Posterior Choroidal Artery" .
