<http://human.owl#genid6533> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "A white blood cell that matures in the primary lymphoid organs and then circulates through the lymph system to the secondary lymphoid tissues where it interacts with antigens. A mature lymphocyte varies in size from 7 to 15 micrometer in diameter and is round or ovoid, but may be notched or slightly indented. The chromatin is generally diffusely dense and nucleoli are not usually visible." .
<http://human.owl#genid6532> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Mature Lymphocyte" .
<http://human.owl#genid4201> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "One of the two permanent teeth located in front of the molars and behind each cuspid. These teeth have two cusps (points) and are used to tear and grind food." .
