<http://human.owl#genid7105> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "The intercalated cell is an epithelial cell of the renal collecting tubule that is specialized for H+ and HCO3 transport. These cells exist in two types, [alpha] and [beta]. The [alpha] cell secretes H+ into the lumen by an apical H+ ATPase and a basolateral Cl:HCO3. The [beta] cell secretes HCO3- into the lumen by an apical Cl:HCO3 and a basolateral H+ ATPase." .
<http://human.owl#genid1290> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Vein Endothelium" .
<http://human.owl#genid7103> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Intercalated Cell" .
<http://human.owl#genid7104> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Dark Cell" .
<http://human.owl#genid4400> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "A cell that is antigenically distinct from other lymphocytes." .
<http://human.owl#genid1292> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Rectum" .
<http://human.owl#genid4401> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Lymphocytes, Allogeneic" .
<http://human.owl#genid7102> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Intercalated Cells" .
<http://human.owl#genid4402> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Allogeneic Lymphocyte" .
