<http://human.owl#genid4463> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Terminally differentiated cells comprising the majority of the external surface of the intestinal epithelium. Unlike goblet cells, they do not produce or secrete mucins, nor do they secrete cryptdins as do the paneth cells. (MeSH)" .
<http://human.owl#genid670> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Tissue composed of three layers- epidermis, dermis and subcutis which protect underlying muscles and organs. Skin is used for insulation, vitamin D production, sensation, and excretion through sweat." .
<http://human.owl#genid671> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Somatostatin Cell of the Pancreas" .
<http://human.owl#genid4447> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Leptomeninges" .
<http://human.owl#genid4448> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "The two innermost layers of tissue that cover the brain and spinal cord, the arachnoid mater and the pia mater." .
