<http://human.owl#genid4455> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Bile ducts are passageways that carry bile. Two major bile ducts come together into a 'trunk'-the common bile duct which empties into the upper part of the small intestine (the part next to the stomach)." .
<http://human.owl#genid4454> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Common Bile Duct" .
