<http://human.owl#genid1254> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Cardiac Vein" .
<http://human.owl#genid1880> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "A lymphocyte found in the marginal zones of lymph nodes. It has a naive B lymphoid lineage and plays an important role in the early phases of immune response with its ability to rapidly differentiate into an antibody secreting cell. These cells can directly activate T cells, interact with other antigen presenting cells, transporting and concentrating antigen during the course of T-dependent and T-independent immune responses." .
