<http://human.owl#genid1863> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Suprarenal gland. A flattened, roughly triangular body resting upon the upper end of each kidney; it is one of the ductless glands furnishing internal secretions (epinephrine and norepinephrine from the medulla and steroid hormones from the cortex). SYN glandula suprarenalis, adrenal body, adrenal capsule, adrenal gland, atrabiliary capsule, epinephros, glandula atrabiliaris, paranephros, suprarenal body, suprarenal capsule." .
<http://human.owl#genid3359> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Common Bony Limb" .
