<http://human.owl#genid7484> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "The smallest anatomical unit of the lung, measuring 0.50 to 2.00 cm in diameter. Each lobule is composed of 4-8 terminal bronchioles and their distal alveolar ducts and sacs. The lobules are separated by fibrous interlobular septa." .
